comments.body:
Thank you. As to not introduce side-effects in other aspects of the site, doing a global `!important` on the `body` is not really something we want to do. In the meantime, I've added the following two methods to the `NavigationMenu.Root`:

```
    onOpenChangeComplete: () => {
      document.body.style.pointerEvents = '';
    }
    onValueChange: () => {
      document.body.style.pointerEvents = '';
    }
```

We can still get the issue to happen, but with these guards in place, we can at least put the mouse cursor back into the submenu and move it out to "unblock" the rest of the site. A more permanent solution would be ideal and any other suggestions you have or might come up with in the future would be much appreciated. Thank you again.
